--> local systems
   --> Docker Desktop
   --> Minikube
   --> Kubeadm

--> hosted versions available for setting up Kubernetes in a cloud environment
	
	--> Google Cloud Platform (GKE)
	--> Amazon Web Service (EKS)
	--> Microsoft Azure (AKS)

--> online platform (for practising)
	--> KodeKloud Playground

Docker Desktop
https://docs.docker.com/desktop/setup/install/windows-install/
Once Installed, enable Kubernetes --> it creates a single node cluster

MiniKube
https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/tools/ 

install kubectl https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/tools/install-kubectl-windows/#install-kubectl-binary-on-windows-via-direct-download-or-curl
(kubectl utility works with multiple clusters at the same time)

install minikube 
https://minikube.sigs.k8s.io/docs/start/?arch=%2Fwindows%2Fx86-64%2Fstable%2F.exe+download

make sure your system has virtualization enabled
